Worker-mode safety: include the backend session identifier in the
FormProtectionFactory cache key.

Under long-running PHP runtimes (FrankenPHP worker mode, RoadRunner,
ReactPHP, …) `cache.runtime` survives across requests. With the original
upstream key — `hash('xxh3', $type)` — every backend request maps to the
same cache entry, so a cached BackendFormProtection from request A is
served back to request B. The cached BFP carries A's memoized
`$sessionToken` and a hard reference to A's BE_USER, and B's form-token
validation runs against A's session secret — surfacing as "Validating
the security token of this form has failed".

Folding the BE_USER's session identifier into the cache key gives each
session its own cached BFP instance. Cross-user requests and
logout/re-login on the same worker no longer collide; under PHP-FPM
nothing changes (the runtime cache dies with the process).

Reported and fixed downstream by EXT:frankenphp
(github.com/ochorocho/typo3-frankenphp). Tracked for upstream merging.

diff --git a/Classes/FormProtection/FormProtectionFactory.php b/Classes/FormProtection/FormProtectionFactory.php
--- a/Classes/FormProtection/FormProtectionFactory.php
+++ b/Classes/FormProtection/FormProtectionFactory.php
@@ -150,7 +150,18 @@ readonly class FormProtectionFactory
      */
     protected function getIdentifierForType(string $type): string
     {
-        return 'formprotection-instance-' . hash('xxh3', $type);
+        // Worker-mode safety: under long-running PHP runtimes (FrankenPHP,
+        // RoadRunner, ReactPHP, …) `cache.runtime` survives across
+        // requests. Keying only by `$type` causes a cached
+        // BackendFormProtection from one session to be served back to
+        // the next request, which then validates its form tokens against
+        // the previous session's `$sessionToken`. Including the backend
+        // session identifier gives each session its own cached instance.
+        $sessionId = '';
+        if ($type === 'backend' && ($GLOBALS['BE_USER'] ?? null) instanceof BackendUserAuthentication) {
+            $sessionId = $GLOBALS['BE_USER']->getSession()?->getIdentifier() ?? '';
+        }
+        return 'formprotection-instance-' . hash('xxh3', $sessionId === '' ? $type : $type . ':' . $sessionId);
     }

     /**
